sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant Server as NeMo Guardrails Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant InputR as Input Rails<br/>(Content Safety, Injection,<br/>Topic Control)
    participant LLM as Upstream LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OutputR as Output Rails<br/>(Hallucination, Factcheck,<br/>Sensitive Data)
    participant OTEL as OpenTelemetry Collector<br/>4317/TCP gRPC

    Note over Client,OTEL: Flow 1: Chat Completion with Guardrails (/v1/chat/completions)

    Client->>Server: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Headers: X-*, Authorization<br/>Body: OpenAI-compat chat request
    activate Server

    Server->>Server: Load Colang flows from<br/>ConfigMap (config.yaml + rails.co)

    rect rgb(255, 235, 235)
        Note over Server,LLM: Input Rail Pipeline
        Server->>InputR: Execute input rails on user message
        InputR->>LLM: Self-check prompt<br/>"Does this contain harmful content?"<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        LLM-->>InputR: Safety evaluation result
        InputR-->>Server: Input rail verdict (pass/fail)
    end

    alt Input Rails PASS
        rect rgb(235, 255, 235)
            Note over Server,LLM: Dialog + Generation Pipeline
            Server->>LLM: Chat completion request<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>Model: MAIN_MODEL_ENGINE
            LLM-->>Server: Generated LLM response
        end

        rect rgb(235, 235, 255)
            Note over Server,LLM: Output Rail Pipeline
            Server->>OutputR: Execute output rails on LLM response
            OutputR->>LLM: Factcheck/hallucination check<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
            LLM-->>OutputR: Evaluation result
            OutputR-->>Server: Output rail verdict (pass/fail)
        end

        alt Output Rails PASS
            Server-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>OpenAI-compat response<br/>(with guardrail metadata)
        else Output Rails FAIL
            Server-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>Canned refusal response<br/>(output blocked by guardrails)
        end
    else Input Rails FAIL
        Server-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>Canned refusal response<br/>(input blocked by guardrails)
    end

    Server->>OTEL: Export trace spans (async)<br/>OTLP protocol

    deactivate Server

    Note over Client,OTEL: Flow 2: Guardrail Checks Only (/v1/guardrail/checks - fork-specific)

    Client->>Server: POST /v1/guardrail/checks<br/>Headers: X-*, Authorization<br/>Body: messages[] with roles
    activate Server

    loop For each message by role
        alt role = user
            Server->>InputR: Run input rails
            InputR->>LLM: Self-check evaluation<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
            LLM-->>InputR: Result
            InputR-->>Server: Per-message verdict
        else role = assistant
            Server->>OutputR: Run output rails
            OutputR->>LLM: Factcheck/safety evaluation<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
            LLM-->>OutputR: Result
            OutputR-->>Server: Per-message verdict
        end
    end

    Server-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>Per-message + aggregate status<br/>(pass/fail per rail)

    Server->>OTEL: Export trace spans (async)

    deactivate Server
